    • Constructor Detail

      • DeadEndGroup

        public DeadEndGroup(INetworkSection obj,
                    Collection<? extends INetworkSection> deadEnds)

        Constructor that builds a dead end group from one element of the group and the set of network edges marked as belonging to dead ends. Be careful, the dead ends of the extorior face are not built.

        Parameters:
        obj - : the network edge used to build the group
        deadEnds - : the set of network edges marked as belonging to dead ends.

      • buildFromRoads

        public static HashSet<DeadEndGroup> buildFromRoads(IFeatureCollection<IRoadLine> roads)
        Builds a set of dead end groups from a road network, using the faces method from Cécile Duchêne. The roads have to be structured as networks with nodes. A border line of the street network can be added to cut the outside sections
        Parameters:
        roads - the roads in which dead ends are searched.
        Returns:
        a set of DeadEndGroup objects

      • buildFromRoads

        public static HashSet<DeadEndGroup> buildFromRoads(IFeatureCollection<IRoadLine> roads,
                                                   IGeometry border)
        Builds a set of dead end groups from a road network, using the faces method from Cécile Duchêne. The roads have to be structured as networks with nodes. A border line of the street network can be added to cut the outside sections
        Parameters:
        roads - the roads in which dead ends are searched.
        borderLine - the outline of the street network
        Returns:
        a set of DeadEndGroup objects
